&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;KINDLED&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kindled:&lt;/strong&gt; It means &lt;strong&gt;awakened&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;em&gt;become impassioned or excited, set (something) on fire, be aroused, ignite.&lt;/em&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Sunita had &lt;strong&gt;kindled &lt;/strong&gt;other fires at her side.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Awakened:&lt;/strong&gt; It means to &lt;em&gt;cause to stop sleeping, rouse from sleeping.&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Gracy was &lt;strong&gt;awakened &lt;/strong&gt;by a noise in the night.&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;From the above meaning, it is evident that &lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;b&gt;wakened&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;same&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;meaning as&amp;nbsp;the word &lt;strong&gt;K&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;indled&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;option 3) Awakened&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;is the correct synonym for the word&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Kindled.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ugly:&lt;/strong&gt; It is the &lt;strong&gt;opposite of beautiful &lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;unpleasant or repulsive, especially in appearance.&lt;/em&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Anuradha is becoming &lt;strong&gt;ugly &lt;/strong&gt;as her age is passing on.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Awkward:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;causing difficulty; hard to do or deal with.&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Salena is a very &lt;strong&gt;awkward &lt;/strong&gt;girl.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Untidy:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;not arranged neatly and in order, disordered, disorganized.&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Ujjwal always does his work in an&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;untidy &lt;/strong&gt;manner.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Ambassador&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate meaning of the given group of words is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Ambassador&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It means&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;an important person who represents his/her country in a foreign country&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt; (राजदूत; विदेश में किसी देश का आधिकारिक प्रतिनिधि)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;the Indian &lt;strong&gt;Ambassador&lt;/strong&gt; to Britain...&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Ambassador.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of other words:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anarchist&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a person who believes in or tries to bring about anarchy. (अराजकतावादी)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alienist&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a psychiatrist who assesses the competence of a defendant in a law court. (एक मनोचिकित्सक जो एक कानून अदालत में प्रतिवादी की क्षमता का आकलन करता है)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theist&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a person who believes in the existence of a god or gods, specifically of a creator who intervenes in the universe. (आस्तिक)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Elegy&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Elegy&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is&amp;nbsp;a sad poem or song, especially remembering someone who has died or something in the past. (शोकगीत)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Gray&amp;#39;s &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Elegy&lt;/strong&gt; Written in a Country Churchyard&amp;quot; is a famous English poem.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Synonyms of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;elegy&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; are &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;lament&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;dirge&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;plaint&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;requiem&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;elegy&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the most appropriate word for the given meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&lt;strong&gt; option 4&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s explore the given options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Sonnet&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is&amp;nbsp;a poem of fourteen lines using any of a number of formal rhyme schemes, in English typically having ten syllables per line. (गाथा)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Hymn&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is a&amp;nbsp;religious song or poem of praise to God. (भजन)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Epitaph&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is a&amp;nbsp;phrase or form of words written in memory of a person who has died, especially as an inscription on a tombstone. (समाधि-लेख)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Clear&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;ambiguous&amp;#39; means &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;having or expressing more than one possible meaning, sometimes intentionally, and therefore not clear&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;Do not be general or &lt;strong&gt;ambiguous&lt;/strong&gt;, be specific and brief while writing your answers&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Antonyms of this word would be &lt;em&gt;unambiguous, clear, lucid, direct, explicit, etc&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s have a look at the definition and examples&amp;nbsp;of the words given in the options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bright &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;giving out or reflecting much light; shining. It may also mean intelligent and quick-witted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Usage example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;The sky was clear and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;bright&lt;/strong&gt; stars shone out here and there in it&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clear &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;easy to perceive, understand or interpret&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Usage example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;The sky was &lt;strong&gt;clear &lt;/strong&gt;and a&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt; mild cool breeze blew from the south&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Faded &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;gradually grows faint and disappear.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Usage example, &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The smile &lt;strong&gt;faded&lt;/strong&gt; from his face when he saw his mother coming towards him with a cane in her hand&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unclear &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;not easy to see, hear, or understand.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Usage example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;It is still unclear to me why she overreacted&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From above, we can refer that the correct choice as an antonym of the given word &amp;#39;ambiguous&amp;#39; is &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clear&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Occupation&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The bracketed phrase&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;a work that would give me income&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is referring to an activity, particularly a regular and continuous one, that provides livelihood.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Out of the alternatives given, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Occupation&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; accurately captures the sense of the phrase. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Occupation refers to the regular job or profession that earns you a living.(पेशा)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the&lt;strong&gt; correct answer&lt;/strong&gt; is:&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Occupation&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Activity:&lt;/strong&gt; This term refers to the state or quality of being involved in a particular task.(गतिविधि)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calling: &lt;/strong&gt;While &amp;quot;calling&amp;quot; can refer to an occupation, particularly in the sense of a higher purpose or passion, it does not necessarily imply generating income. (बुलावा)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pursuit:&lt;/strong&gt; This term is the act of pursuing, in general can refer to an occupation, hobby, or preoccupation, but the term lacks the specific implication of earning a livelihood. (अन्वेषण)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Recurrent&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate word for the given group of words is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Recurrent&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recuperate&lt;/strong&gt; - to recover from illness or exertion (उपचार करना / ठीक होना)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recurrent&lt;/strong&gt; - happening repeatedly or frequently (बार-बार होनेवाला)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rapport&lt;/strong&gt; - a close and harmonious relationship in which the people or groups concerned understand each other&amp;#39;s feelings or ideas and communicate well (मिलनसारता / सबसे अच्छी दोस्ती)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regression&lt;/strong&gt; - a return to a former or less developed state (प्रतिष्ठान / पीछे हटना)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct answer is option&lt;strong&gt; 2) Recurrent.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given context, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;recurrent&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; best describes something happening repeatedly. &lt;em&gt;For example, &amp;quot;The &lt;strong&gt;recurrent&lt;/strong&gt; power outages in the area have caused inconvenience to the residents.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is- &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Paid for by someone&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate meaning of the given idiom&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;At somebody&amp;#39;s expense&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;​​Paid for by someone&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s look at the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;meaning and example&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given phrasal verb:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;At somebody&amp;#39;s expense&lt;/span&gt;- &amp;quot;If you do something at someone&amp;#39;s expense, they provide the money for it&amp;quot;.(&lt;span style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;किसी के द्वारा भुगतान किया गया&lt;span style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;)
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E.g.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Her mansion was refurbished &lt;strong&gt;at taxpayers&amp;rsquo; expense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​​&lt;/em&gt;Thus from the explanation given above, we find that the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;3rd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;option&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct choice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Perplexed.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the idiom&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At one&amp;rsquo;s wit&amp;#39;s end&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is c&lt;/span&gt;ompletely puzzled and perplexed, not knowing what to do.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Idiom&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;At one&amp;rsquo;s wit&amp;#39;s end&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; का अर्थ पूरी तरह से हैरान और हैरान करने वाला है, न जाने क्या-क्या।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;I&amp;#39;ve tried every possible source without success, and now I&amp;#39;m &lt;strong&gt;at my wit&amp;#39;s end&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct option is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Perplexed.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The meaning of the word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enlighten&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is to give&amp;nbsp;(someone) greater knowledge and understanding about a subject or situation.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;Christopher had not &lt;strong&gt;enlightened &lt;/strong&gt;Francis as to their relationship.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Ethnology&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate word for the given group of words is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Ethnology&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It means&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;the scientific study and comparison of human races;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;the branch of anthropology that deals with races and peoples, their relations to one another, their origins, and their distinctive characteristics.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;(मानव जातियों का वैज्ञानिक अध्ययन; नृजाति विज्ञान)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;He settled in Berlin, where he was made professor of &lt;strong&gt;ethnology&lt;/strong&gt; at the university and keeper of the ethnological museum.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Ethnology.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of other words:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anthropology&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;the study of human beings, especially of their origin, development, customs and beliefs. (मानव की उत्&amp;zwj;पत्ति, उसके विकास, प्रथाओं और विश्&amp;zwj;वासों का वैज्ञानिक अध्ययन; मानव-विज्ञान)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Etymology&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;the history of a word or phrase shown by tracing its development and relationships. (शब्द-साधन)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Archaeology&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;the study of the past, based on objects or parts of buildings that are found in the ground. (ज़मीन के भीतर पाए गए प्राचीन वस्तुओं एवं भवनों के अवशेष पर आधारित अतीत का अध्ययन; पुरातत्व विज्ञान)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2 i.e. Impossible to return to an earlier state.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Burn one&amp;#39;s bridges&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;means to do something that makes it impossible to go back to the previous situation.&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; After arguing with his boss and quitting his job so abruptly, Jake realized he had burned his bridges and&amp;nbsp;ask for his job back.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct meaning of the idiom, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Impossible to return to an earlier state,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; refers to a situation or action from which one cannot return or revert.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; When she publicly criticized her company in social media, she effectively burned her bridges with her employer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;correct answer&lt;/strong&gt; is- &amp;#39;Impossible to return to an earlier state.&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1:&lt;/strong&gt; Working very hard&amp;nbsp; refers to putting a lot of effort into a task. This does not relate to the idiom&amp;#39;s meaning of making a situation irreversible.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3: &lt;/strong&gt;Having an overnight success&amp;nbsp;implies achieving success very quickly, which is unrelated to the concept of burning one&amp;#39;s bridges.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4: &lt;/strong&gt;Attack on oneundefineds enemy suggests a direct confrontation or aggression towards an adversary, which is not connected to the irreversible decision implied by the idiom.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;niggardly&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;generous&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;happy to give more money, help, etc. than is usual or expected&lt;/strong&gt;. (असामान्&amp;zwj;य या अप्रत्&amp;zwj;याशित रूप से धन, सहायता आदि देने में प्रसन्&amp;zwj;नता अनुभव करने वाला)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​Let&amp;#39;s see the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of other given options:-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Niggardly&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ungenerous with money, time, etc.; mean&lt;/strong&gt;. (पैसे, समय, आदि के साथ अनैतिक; लालची)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Selfish&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;thinking only about your own needs or wishes and not about other people&amp;rsquo;s&lt;/strong&gt;. (स्&amp;zwj;वार्थी, ख़ुदग़रज़)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Spendthrift&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;a person who spends a lot of money carelessly or wastes money&lt;/strong&gt;. (लापरवाही से पैसे ख़र्च करनेवाला; फ़िज़ूलख़र्च)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indecent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;not appropriate or fitting&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;(अशोभनीय, अश्&amp;zwj;लील)&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;generous&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;niggardly,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;selfish, cheap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;synonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;generous&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;extravagant,&amp;nbsp;lavish, kind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Example&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;of&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;generous​&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;in a&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;They made a &lt;strong&gt;generous&lt;/strong&gt; donation to charity&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;b&gt;Important&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trivial&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;refers to something that has very little value or importance.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;She cries over something very trivial.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Important&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;refers to something that is necessary or of great value.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;She has some important work to do.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​&lt;strong&gt;Trivial&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Important&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;have different meanings.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct option is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Important.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bashful&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;refers to frequently feeling awkward among others and being easily embarrassed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Civil&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;refers to something that is not military, religious or pertaining to the general populace of a nation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naughty&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is used as a lighthearted reference to characterise an adult who has acted inappropriately or an adult&amp;#39;s poor behaviour.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;Prompt&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Decisive: Making a decision or taking action without hesitation or delay. (बिना किसी हिचकिचाहट या देरी के निर्णय लेना या कार्रवाई करना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Example sentence: The decisive action of the fire department saved many lives during the fire.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence mentions the government&amp;#39;s decisive action in handling the crisis, which implies taking prompt and resolute steps to address the situation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;Option 3&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hesitant: Uncertain or lacking confidence. (अनिश्चित या आत्मविश्वास की कमी)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Uncertain: Not certain or definite. (निश्चित या निश्चित नहीं)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ambiguous: Open to more than one interpretation. (एक से अधिक व्याख्याओं के लिए खुला)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is Option (2) i.e. &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;In full view of somebody&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Under the nose&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; of someone: To do something openly or in such close proximity that it&amp;#39;s easily observable by others (किसी की पूरी दृष्टि में कुछ करना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: The thief managed to steal the painting right &lt;strong&gt;under the nose&lt;/strong&gt; of the security guards.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In full view of somebody: &lt;/strong&gt;(किसी की पूर्ण दृष्टि में)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: He completed the magic trick under the nose of the amazed audience.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This Option 2 directly reflects the idiom&amp;#39;s meaning related to doing something openly or in such a manner that it can easily be witnessed by others around.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;In full view of somebody&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;After much persuasion:&lt;/strong&gt; This implies that an action was taken as a result of considerable convincing, which doesn&amp;#39;t directly relate to the idiom&amp;#39;s implication of doing something openly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sharing equally:&lt;/strong&gt; This option denotes distributing something in equal parts among people, which does not align with the idiom&amp;#39;s context of the visibility of an action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secretly:&lt;/strong&gt; The idea of doing something secretly is opposite to the idiom&amp;rsquo;s actual meaning of performing an action openly or in full view of others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is -&lt;strong&gt; Ordinary.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate antonym of &amp;quot;outstanding&amp;quot; is &amp;quot;ordinary.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;Outstanding&amp;quot; means &lt;strong&gt;exceptional, excellent, or remarkable&lt;/strong&gt;. The opposite or antonym of &amp;quot;outstanding&amp;quot; would be a word that means average, ordinary, or unremarkable.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Astounding&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; means surprising or shocking, which is not the opposite of outstanding.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Ordinary&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; means plain, average, or usual, which is the most appropriate antonym of outstanding.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Remarkable&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is a synonym of outstanding, not its antonym.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Honest&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; means truthful or sincere, which is not related to the meaning of outstanding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, option 2) &lt;strong&gt;Ordinary &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct antonym of the given word &amp;quot;outstanding.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

