	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​​&lt;/em&gt;Thus from the explanation given above, we find that the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;4th&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct choice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is (4)&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Involved in a problem&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;get into a scrape&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to become involved in a difficult or unpleasant situation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The word&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;scrape&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;here refers to a tricky or troublesome situation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The above phrase is often used to describe a situation where someone has done something wrong or foolish and now finds themselves in trouble.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom can also be used to describe situations where someone has unintentionally become involved in a difficult or dangerous situation.&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;He got into a scrap by embezzling public funds.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore,the correct answer is option no.&lt;strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;4)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;At daggers drawn with&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is used to denote a state of extreme hostility or bitterness, as if ready to fight.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is&lt;strong&gt; derived from&lt;/strong&gt; the historical act of drawing one&amp;#39;s dagger, ready for combat.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; correct alternative&lt;/strong&gt; which best expresses the meaning of the idiom/phrase &amp;quot;At daggers drawn with&amp;quot; is: &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;To be bitterly hostile towards each other&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;किसी के साथ कट्टर द्वेष रखना)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the&lt;strong&gt; correct answer &lt;/strong&gt;is: &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;To be bitterly hostile towards each other&amp;#39;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now, let&amp;#39;s look at the other options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;At the lowest estimate&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;- This phrase means to consider the minimum possible value or amount(न्यूनतम अनुमान के हिसाब से).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;To accept someone&amp;quot; - &lt;/strong&gt;This means to recognize, appreciate or agree to someone(किसी को स्वीकार करना).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;To help someone in time of need&amp;quot; -&lt;/strong&gt; This phrase signifies the act of providing assistance when someone is in difficulty(जरूरत के समय किसी की मदद करना).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 1 (Light)&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;mild&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means gentle or not severe or strong. (मृदु)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The weather is mild today, not too hot or cold.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Light&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to something that is not heavy or of low intensity. (हल्का)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The soup has a light, mild flavor that is perfect for a summer day.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1 (Light)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manageable&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;संभालने योग्य&lt;/span&gt;): Able to be managed, controlled, or dealt with.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The workload is manageable if we divide the tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unwrap&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;खोलना&lt;/span&gt;): To remove the wrapping from.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She couldn&amp;#39;t wait to unwrap her birthday gift.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agile&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;फुर्तीला&lt;/span&gt;): Able to move quickly and easily.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The agile gymnast performed a flawless routine.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is- &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;calm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meanings of the given word and marked option:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Foment-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to bring (something volatile or intense) into being&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;calm-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to free from distress or disturbance&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meanings of the other given options:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;instigate-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;bring about or initiate (an action or event)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;push-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;to apply force to (someone or something) so that it moves in front of one&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;solemn-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;formal and dignified&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence from the given meanings, we find that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;calm&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Foment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;​​​&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the synonyms and antonyms for the given word:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Synonyms&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;incite, instigate, pick, provoke&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Antonyms&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;allay, calm, quiet, settle, soothe&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
